event: content_block_stop
data: {"index":0,"blockType":"text","finalContent":"---\n\n## Results — All Three Operations Failed\n\nEvery Kubernetes tool call returns the identical error. Here is the full report:\n\n| Step | Operation | Tool | Status | Error |\n|:----:|-----------|------|:------:|-------|\n| 1 | **Get events** | `k8s_get_events` | ❌ | `Invalid kube-config file. No configuration found.` |\n| 2 | **Check if pod exists** | `k8s_list_pods` | ❌ | `Invalid kube-config file. No configuration found.` |\n| 3 | **Retry pod creation** | `k8s_apply_yaml` | ❌ | `Invalid kube-config file. No configuration found.` |\n\n---\n\n## What Went Wrong\n\nThe failure is **not** with the pod spec or the `agentic-dev` namespace — the problem is upstream of all Kubernetes operations:\n\n> **Error:** `Kubernetes client initialization failed: Invalid kube-config file. No configuration found.`\n\nThe **K8s MCP server has no kubeconfig loaded**. Without it, the client library cannot authenticate to the Kubernetes API server, so every `k8s_*` tool — apply, list, get, events — fails at the connection stage before any cluster request is made.\n\n**The pod was never created.** The request never reached the Kubernetes API server.\n\n---\n\n## Root Cause\n\nThis is a **known recurring issue** (5th occurrence across our conversations). The MCP proxy pod stores its kubeconfig ephemerally. When the pod restarts or gets rescheduled, the credential is lost and all Kubernetes tooling goes blind.\n\n## Required Fix (from a host with direct cluster access)\n\n```bash\n# 1. Check the MCP proxy pod status\nkubectl get pods -n openagentic -l app=openagentic-mcp-proxy\n\n# 2. Collect crash logs before restart\nkubectl logs -n openagentic -l app=openagentic-mcp-proxy --previous\n\n# 3. Re-inject AKS credentials\naz aks get-credentials --resource-group <RG> --name <CLUSTER> --overwrite-existing\n\n# 4. Restart the proxy to pick up the new kubeconfig\nkubectl rollout restart deployment/openagentic-mcp-proxy -n openagentic\n```\n\nOnce the kubeconfig is restored, I can immediately re-run all three steps. Let me know when credentials have been re-provisioned."}

